University Admission Prediction¶

This project analyze the dataset from https://www.kaggle.com/mohansacharya/graduate-admissions and predicts if a student will get an admission (on based on his/her GRE score, GPA score and University rank) to university or not.

The dataset contains several parameters which are considered important during the application for Masters Programs. The parameters included are :

GRE Scores ( out of 340 )

TOEFL Scores ( out of 120 )

University Rating ( out of 5 )

Statement of Purpose and Letter of Recommendation Strength ( out of 5 )

Undergraduate GPA ( out of 10 )

Research Experience ( either 0 or 1 )

Chance of Admit ( ranging from 0 to 1 ) is the Target Variable

Find the overall accuracy with different Sklearn Machine learning modules like

Linear Regression

Random Forest Classifier

Support Vector Machine

XG BOOST

DecisionTreeRegressor

MODEL¶

Here we are going to develop the models Linear Regression, Random Forest Classifier, Support Vector Machine, XG BOOST, Decision Tree Regressor and train the model on the testing dataset and then fit the trained model on the testing dataset and append the values of accuracy, root mean squared error and r squared value and convert them into a dataframe and choose the model

The mean squared error is defiend as the square root of the mean squared error between the real values and the predicited values

Decalring empty lists for accuracy, root mean squared error and r squared value and save the model name

In [43]:
accuracy=[]
rmse=[]
r2=[]
model_name=[]
